              },
              "free_text": [
                " The back-streaming white neutron",
                "beamline (Back-n) at the China Spallation Neutron",
                "Source (CSNS)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons are produced via 1.6 GeV proton-",
                "induced spallation reactions on a Tungsten target.",
                "The incident proton pulse was in double-bunch mode,",
                "about 60 ns (FWHM) wide and 410 ns apart."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "94-PU-239",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9671
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two uranium and two plutonium",
                "samples were used in this measurement. The plutonium",
                "samples were electroplated on platinum backings. The",
                "uranium samples were electroplated on the stainless",
                "steel and aluminium backing. The mass of the two",
                "plutonium samples were 373 and 401 ug. The diameter",
                "of the two plutonium samples were 25.4 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A fast fission ionization chamber for the",
                "fission cross section measurement was mounted at the",
                "endstation 1 of Back-n. The chamber is a cylinder",
                "made of 5 mm-thick aluminium alloy with length of 300",
                "mm and diameter of 300 mm. The neutron window with",
                "diameter of 80 mm was sealed with 100 um Kapton film",
                "at the center of chamber caps. The chamber was filled",
                "with a mixture gas of 90% Ar and 10% CF4 at a",
                "pressure of 800 mbar. A stack of fission cells was",
                "mounted inside the chamber along the neutron beam",
                "direction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A flight path about 57 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": {
