                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Detection efficiency and sample mass."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "2",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "MONIT-ERR",
                "minimum_value": 0.6,
                "maximum_value": 3.6,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties of the",
                "235U(n,f) cross sections are provided by IAEA",
                "standards which vary from about 0.6% to about 3.6% in",
                "the range from 4 keV to 100 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The correction due to isotopic composition and",
                "neutron flux attenuation. The correction factor for",
                "isotopic composition substantially keeps as 1 when",
                "the neutron energy is less than 400 keV, apart from",
                "some resonance dips. When the energy is above 400 keV,",
                "the correction factor decreases with the increasing",
                "of neutron energy and then becomes steady around",
                "1MeV. The flux attenuation tends to be more severe,",
                "especially in the low-energy region with the increase",
                "of the material amount."
              ]
            }
          ],
